ESSAY: 

Define the following terms in your own words (including, where applicable, stating what the term stands for) :

Version control
VCS
TFS
Branch
Merge

Version Control: The process of saving snapshots of you files as you work on them over time so you can go back to them if/when the need arises and to make collaboration run smoothly.

VCS: (version control system) A program used for version control.

TFS: (team foundation server) A Microsoft product that provides source code management.

Branch: When you copy a file from the master branch in order to work on it.

Merge: When you combine the branch you were working on to the master branch.

-Brian Miller
